---
import SectionWrapper from "./SectionWrapper.astro";
---

<SectionWrapper id="about">
  <div>
    <h2>About Me</h2>
    <p class="about-text">
      I'm <strong>Adonis Mendoza</strong>, a <strong>Full Stack Developer</strong> who
      started out in <strong>JavaScript</strong> and never really left. I like
      building interfaces from the ground up — hands-on, vanilla first — and
      reaching for <strong>Bootstrap</strong> or a component library only when the
      project actually calls for it. That foundation has shaped how I think
      about every UI I ship: efficient, maintainable, and predictable.
    </p>

    <h3 class="about-subheading">What I work with</h3>
    <p class="about-text">
      On the frontend I ship production apps with <strong>Vue.js</strong> (Vue 2
      and Vue 3 + Pinia). On the backend I design services with
      <strong>AdonisJS</strong> — a Laravel-inspired Node.js framework — backed
      by <strong>MongoDB</strong> or <strong>PostgreSQL</strong> depending on the
      shape of the data. I'm comfortable owning the full slice: REST APIs,
      <strong>WebSockets</strong> and Server-Sent Events for real-time features,
      Redis for caching and pub/sub, and clean
      <strong>hexagonal / DDD-style architectures</strong> when the domain gets
      complex.
    </p>

    <p class="about-text">
      Outside the JavaScript ecosystem I have working knowledge of
      <strong>C#</strong> for backend services and console apps, which lets me
      collaborate across stacks without friction. Most of my recent work has
      been in real-time, high-concurrency platforms — wagering systems, live
      back-offices and dealer tools — where latency, uptime and a clear
      operator UX all matter.
    </p>

    <h3 class="about-subheading">What I'm looking for</h3>
    <p class="about-text">
      I'm open to <strong>full-time</strong> and
      <strong>contract</strong> opportunities as a Full Stack Developer, ideally
      on a product team that cares about both the technical foundation and the
      end-user experience. If you're building something in the
      <strong>Vue.js / Node.js</strong> space and want an extra pair of senior
      hands, let's talk.
    </p>
  </div>
</SectionWrapper>

<style>
  .about-text {
    font-size: var(--fs-body-lg);
    line-height: 1.75;
  }

  .about-subheading {
    font-size: var(--fs-subtitle);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--text-subheading);
    margin: 1.75rem 0 0.5rem;
  }
</style>
